# Install-private machine state (survives git pull; one per machine, spans ALL managed workspaces:
# DB, runs, worktrees, secrets, settings, workspace definition files). The ONLY "local" zone —
# a workspace governance dir (cocoder/) never contains one (ADR-0008 amendment, 2026-06-10).
# `/local/*` + negation keeps the signage README tracked while everything else stays private.
/local/*
!/local/README.md

# Secrets — never tracked at any depth (ARCHITECTURE.md ignore matrix; audit §B7)
*.env
.env.*
secrets/
# Quinn credentials — belt-and-braces against accidental tracking. The canonical
# home is `local/secrets/.quinn-credentials.json` (install-private zone, already
# ignored); this catches mis-placed copies elsewhere in the tree. The
# `*.example.json` template stays tracked (no leading `.`).
.quinn-credentials.json
# Exception: the install-template ships an empty secrets/ directory with its own
# .gitignore so `cocoder init` lays down the correct ignore rule for adopters.
# Without this negation, the `secrets/` rule above would hide that template file.
!templates/install-local/secrets/
!templates/install-local/secrets/.gitignore

# Dependencies and build output
node_modules/
.turbo/
*.tsbuildinfo
# Per-package build output (v2: TS compiles to dist/ per package)
packages/*/dist/

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
.stfolder/
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/settings.json.example
